<HEADLINE>
Anti-Nazi Coup, 1933
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> gpmayn...@comcast.net </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-10-08T21:35:00 </POSTDATE>
General Kurt von Schleicher was a close confidante of President
Hindenburg, and the last Chancellor of the Weimar Republic prior to
Hitler's becoming chancellor.  He had a plan in '33 to create a
permanent government through the declaration of marital law and the
suppression of the Communists and elements of the Nazi Party.  He
planned to unite the left Nazis- led by the Strasser brothers, and the
Social Democratic and Christian labor unions, in order to rule the
country under emergency decree but with those groups support.
Essentially he planned to destroy the extreme left and right, leaving
a more agreeable center, from which a more stable government could be
built.  His plan obviously failed because he lost Hindenburg's support
to von Papen's plan to bring Hitler into government.
In this POD he gains Hindenburg's support and declares martial law.
Hitler realizes what is happening and mobilizes his party supporters,
as do the Communists.  Schleicher has called out the Army to enforce
the martial law and his emergency decrees and orders the arrest of the
leaders of both the Communist and Nazi Parties.  Special &quot;Emergency
Tribunals&quot; are held and the Nazi and Communist Party leadership is
accused of plotting a coup against the Republic.  When the dust clears
Schleicher is still Chancellor now ruling by decree but has managed to
create a government from representatives of the above mentioned
groups.  Gregor Strasser assumes control of the Nazi party, the pro-
Hitler leadership having been swept aside, and the Communist party is
outlawed.  For the next several years there is continued unrest from
hard-core Nazis and Communists.
With Schleicher having averted a Nazi takeover how will Germany
evolve from here?
</POST>
