About 30 minutes after Schleicher announces his coup, he is confronted
by the heads of the departments of the General Staff. He was shot by
General Werner von Blomberg and died instantly. The Army summoned
Fritz von Papen, who had the confiedence of President Hindenberg, and
announced a government of the Army to be headed by von Papen as
Chancellor. The left ranks of the Nazi party were decimated in street
fighting and Hitler, Goering, Rohm and other high level Nazis were
imprisoned, tried and hung as traitors.

The military-led Germany government concentrated on rebuilding the
Army and creating an atmosphere of trust with their neighbors. The
Strasbourg Conference of 1934 returned the Rhineland to Germany and a
modus vivendi with Poland provided German access to East Prussia.

German &quot;volunteers&quot; participated in the Spanish Civil War as part of
the Franco forces. Several weapons systems were given trials in this
encounter, many faults with the aviation and armor led to closer
relations with the Soviet Union, which the German military had used as
a training ground since the 1920s.

When Italy invaded Ethiopia the small contingent of German troops sent
by the League of Nations was instrumental in securing the port of
Eritrea and enabling the British force to counteract the Italians.
